node.text:
As our planet warms, droughts/floods persist, ancient glaciers melt & wildfire smoke chokes the atmosphere we begin to feel the true effects of climate change - ocean acidification, ozone layer depletion & loss of biodiversity across the globe all the while an absurd amount of pollution continues to be released into the air, water & soil.
While 40% of the world’s population lives within 100 kilometers (62 miles) of the coast, many of us inland aren’t reminded of the importance of our coral reefs.
 
Home to over 25% of marine life, coral reefs are one of the most biodiverse ecosystems on Earth, and they play an important role in the health of millions of species, including humans.
However, rising ocean temperatures and acidification due to greenhouse gas emissions have put coral reefs at risk of worldwide collapse within the next decade. @seed’s ecological research division, SeedLabs, is partnering with Dr. Raquel Peixoto, Associate Professor of Marine Biology at @kaustofficial to research the development of coral probiotics and the necessary delivery technologies to conserve, restore and protect coral reefs against the impact of anthropogenic climate change. It’s important we continue to educate ourselves & remain aware of the threats we face while staying hopeful, positive & optimistic about our collective ability to create change for the future. Visit the link in my bio to learn more! #ad #SeedPartner @seed 🐠
